 a village, from Middle French <i>bourg</i> (Old French <i>burc</i>) ‘fortified town’, or a habitational name from (Le) Bourg, the name of several places in various parts of France. Compare   Bourke  ,   Bourque  ,   Burk  , and   Burke  .","History: Antoine Bourg/Bourque from Martaizé in Vienne, France, married Antoinette Landry in Acadia <i>c.</i> 1642. His descendants also bear altered forms of the surname, such as <i>Bourke</i>, <i>Bourque</i>, and <i>Burk(e)</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Bourgeois","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Marcel, Emile, Alphonse, Armand, Camille, Gaston, Monique, Pierre, Lucien, Michel, Normand.","French: from <i>bourgeois</i> ‘burgher’ (from Old French <i>burgeis</i>, from <i>burc</i> ‘fortified town’), a status name for an inhabitant and (usually) freeman of a fortified town (see   Bourg  ). Compare   Lebourgeois   and also   Boss  ,   Burgess  , and   Bushway  .","History: Jacques Bourgeois from France married Jeanne Trahan in Acadia <i>c.</i> 1643. Pierre Bourgeois from Poligny in Jura, France, married Marie-Louise Cléroux in Saint-Vincent-de-Paul, QC, in 1753."]},{"name":"Bourke","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Dermot, Liam, Murphy.","Irish: variant of   Burke  .","Americanized form of French   Bourg   or of its altered form   Bourque  ."]},{"name":"Bourget","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Normand, Jacques, Lucien, Pierre, Aime, Andre, Fernand, Germaine, Laurent, Ludger, Marcel, Marcell.","French: topographic name, a diminutive of   Bourg  , or a habitational name from (Le) Bourget, the name of several places in various parts of France.","Altered form of French <b>Bourgeais</b>, a variant of   Bourgeois  ."]},{"name":"Boulerice","meanings":["Altered form of Breton <b>Bourhis</b>: from <i>bourc'his</i> ‘burgher’, a status name for an inhabitant and (usually) freeman of a fortified town (see   Bourg  , compare   Bourgeois  )."]},{"name":"Bourque","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Lucien, Pierre, Andre, Aurele, Camille, Emile, Fernand, Henri, Jacques, Marcel, Normand.","French (mainly Doubs): variant of   Bourg   and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this.","History: The (majority of the) American bearers of the surname <i>Bourque</i> are descendants of Antoine Bourg/Bourque from France (see   Bourg  )."]}]},{"name":"Auguste","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin.  See  <b>Augustus</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Auguste de Bours was born in 1176, his father, Pasquet De Bours, was 51 and his mother, Michelle de Nedonchel, was 23. He married Marguerite de Grigny in 1204, in Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1230, at the age of 54."},"et":{"1176–1230":"1176–1230","1173–1231":"1173–1231","1174–1248":"1174–1248","1179–1225":"1179–1225","1185–1250":"1185–1250","1207–1259":"1207–1259","1125–1187":"1125–1187","1153–1189":"1153–1189","1176":"1176","1187":"1187","1231":"1231","1230":"1230","1153":"1153","1185":"1185","1174":"1174","1250":"1250","1173":"1173","1204":"1204","1259":"1259","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","1125":"1125","1179":"1179","1189":"1189","1207":"1207","Grigny, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1176–1230":"1176–1230","1173–1231":"1173–1231","1174–1248":"1174–1248","1179–1225":"1179–1225","1185–1250":"1185–1250","1207–1259":"1207–1259","1125–1187":"1125–1187","1153–1189":"1153–1189","1176":"1176","1187":"1187","1231":"1231","1230":"1230","1153":"1153","1185":"1185","1174":"1174","1250":"1250","1173":"1173","1204":"1204","1259":"1259","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","1125":"1125","1179":"1179","1189":"1189","1207":"1207","Grigny, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Ranska"},"fr":{"1176–1230":"1176–1230","1173–1231":"1173–123